===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|dum|nl}} ''loy'', ''leuy''.
Cognate with the Old Norse adjective {{term|lúinn|lang=non}} “exhausted”, the Latin noun {{term|lues|luēs|lang=la|epidemy}} and the Ancient Greek verb {{term|λύω|sc=polytonic|lang=grc}} “I untie”.<ref>de Vries / de Tollenaere, "Etymologisch Woordenboek", Utrecht 1986 (14de druk), ISBN 90-274-3459-X; article ''lui 2''</ref>

